<span class="name"><a name="95918"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#51:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Wyora</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=95918#95918"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Mon Feb 07, 2005 2:26 pm</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I know this is an old post, but something happened a couple of weeks ago that seemed perfect for it.  I've been raiding with one of the top guilds on my server for a while, and recently app'd to them.  We're doing our typical thing of starting off in Qvic.  I'm being a good recruit and sitting on the bridge in KT with a few other people, waiting to get 85'd in.  Raid leader pops across, invites us to the raid, and tells us to zone over.  No mage available for CoH  <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" />   But we had a rogue available to drag us  <img src="images/smiles/icon_confused.gif" alt="icon_confused.gif" border="0" />   Our instructions were to invis and run as far as we could before dying, then consent the rogue.
<br />

<br />
I pop on black beauty, invis myself and the 2 other people getting ready for the suicide run.  Run horse, run!  I see the other 2 people die, but for some strange reason I'm still at 100% health.  Yay!  I keep on running.  Hmm, I'm getting pretty close to the raid.  I can actually see the raid.  I'll be nice and stop right out here in front of them so they don't have far to drag my corpse, I should be far enough away that my train of about 20 mobs won't agro them.
<br />

<br />
Well, guess what.  Those 20 mobs decided to path right on top of the raid before they reset.  I can't claim a full wipe as a bard lived.  Needless to say, I wasn't the favorite recruit that night. <img src="images/smiles/icon_hang.gif" alt="icon_hang.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
