<span class="name"><a name="96273"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#52:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Jeradim</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=96273#96273"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Thu Feb 10, 2005 1:17 pm</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">OK I finally got one.  This just happened the night before last.  I'm not a 100% sure it was my fault but I'll post it anyway.
<br />

<br />
We were doing a Seru raid.  I 2-box all the time with my Mage and usually have him auto-following me.  I like to go first because I figure if 1 of us is to get jumped then I have a few more defenses than he does (i.e. >2 - pet and gate).  I don't know if my UI files have gone wonky or if I can chalk it all up to lag or what, but he quite often ends up running in big circles around me if I stop rather than just stopping behind me like he's supposed to.  So on the Seru raid we enter his room and I turn immediately left to head to the corner and start mezzing the adds.  The idea here is not to aggro Seru.  
<br />
Well as I said the auto-follow is kinda quirky and it happens a lot that Jeradim goes wandering off so I was half expecting it.  I'm pretty sure I caught him before he got onto Seru's platform but all I know is Seru aggro'd the raid and we all wiped (got revenge after though).  I was kind of busy mezzing so I didn't see but I think someone may have pushed one of the Praetorians near Seru's platform and that's how it happened, but since he aggro'd right after my little auto-follow mishap I thought it was me at first.  I was mortified and it was right after the GL/RL specifically and quite clearly stated not to go near Seru's platform (which we all knew already which made it even more n00bish and embarrasing)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
